# Purchases – List User Purchases
# Smoke tests for GET /users/me/purchases.
#
# Authenticated-user endpoint. Returns a paginated list of purchases belonging
# to the currently authenticated user, enriched with merchant names.
# Supports optional filtering by status (pending, confirmed, reversed).
# Run the helper login request below to obtain a fresh token.
#
# Seed data (seeds/all.sql):
#   Alice (b7e2c1a2-4f3a-4e2b-9c1a-8d2e3f4b5c6d) has 7 purchases:
#     txn_seed_001 – pending,   Shoply,    100.00 EUR
#     txn_seed_002 – pending,   Shoply,     50.00 EUR
#     txn_seed_005 – confirmed, Shoply,    300.00 EUR
#     txn_seed_007 – pending,   QuickCart,  80.00 EUR
#     txn_seed_009 – pending,   TechZone,   60.00 EUR
#     txn_seed_reject_001 – pending, BankSimFail, 99.00 EUR
#   (total 6 regular + 1 rejection-sim = 7 rows, enough to test pagination)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8001/api/v1

# Expired local-dev placeholder — never a real credential.
@userToken = Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoiYjdlMmMxYTItNGYzYS00ZTJiLTljMWEtOGQyZTNmNGI1YzZkIiwidXNlcl9yb2xlIjoidXNlciIsImV4cCI6MTc3MzU1NDIyNH0.zK4IUYa_zjRzQ4lQW5NRffTCSiBO2rhzuf3OciuuP30

### Helper – obtain a fresh user token (alice)
# Returns access_token — paste as "Bearer <token>" into @userToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

### 200 – Happy path: list all purchases (default page)
# Alice has 7 seed purchases. Expects a paginated envelope with total >= 7 and
# items containing merchant_name, amount, status, cashback_amount, cashback_status.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by status=pending
# Expects only alice's purchases with status=pending (txn_seed_001, 002, 007, 009 and
# the rejection-sim row). cashback_status will be null until the cashback module is wired.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?status=pending
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by status=confirmed
# Expects only alice's confirmed purchase (txn_seed_005, 300.00 EUR at Shoply).
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?status=confirmed
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: filter by status=reversed
# Alice has no reversed purchases; expects an empty paginated list.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?status=reversed
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: pagination – offset=0, limit=3
# Verifies that items are limited to 3 and total reflects the full count.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?offset=0&limit=3
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: pagination – offset=3, limit=3
# Verifies offset is applied; returns purchases 4-6 of alice's purchases.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?offset=3&limit=3
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: offset beyond total (empty data)
# Large offset with default limit guarantees no results.
# Expects: {"data": [], "pagination": {"offset": 990, "limit": 10, "total": <actual_total>}}
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?offset=990
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 401 – Sad path: unauthenticated request
# No Authorization header — auth middleware rejects before the handler is reached.
# Expects: 401 UNAUTHORIZED.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases

### 422 – Sad path: invalid status filter value
# status=badvalue is not in [pending, confirmed, reversed].
# Expects: 422 with error code INVALID_PURCHASE_STATUS.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?status=badvalue
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 422 – Sad path: offset below minimum (offset=-1)
# Schema constraint: offset must be >= 0.
# Expects: 422 VALIDATION_ERROR with field=offset.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?offset=-1
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 422 – Sad path: limit below minimum (limit=0)
# Schema constraint: limit must be >= 1.
# Expects: 422 VALIDATION_ERROR with field=limit.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?limit=0
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 422 – Sad path: limit above maximum (limit=101)
# Schema constraint: limit must be <= 100.
# Expects: 422 VALIDATION_ERROR with field=limit.
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?limit=101
Authorization: {{userToken}}
